SQL Case Study Projects (Hotel & Clinic Analytics)
Project Overview:-

This repository contains two real-world SQL case studies:

1.Hotel Management System
2.Clinic Business Analytics

Each project includes:

Database Schema Design
Sample Data Insertion
Advanced SQL Queries for Analysis

Project Structure SQL-Case-Studies
  01_Hotel_Schema_Setup.sql
  02_Hotel_Queries.sql
  03_Clinic_Schema_Setup.sql
  04_Clinic_Queries.sql
  README.md

1.Hotel Management System
=>Files:
Schema Setup →Queries →Database Tables
users → Customer details
bookings → Room bookings
items → Food/menu items
booking_commercials → Billing details

Key SQL Problems Solved
Latest booking per user
Monthly revenue calculation
High-value bills filtering
Most & least ordered items
Second highest bill per month

=>Concepts Used
Joins (INNER JOIN)
Window Functions (ROW_NUMBER, RANK)
Aggregations (SUM, GROUP BY)
CTEs (WITH clause)

2.Clinic Business Analytics
=>Files:
Schema Setup →Queries →Database Tables
clinics → Clinic details
customer → Customer data
clinic_sales → Revenue data
expenses → Expense tracking

=> Key SQL Problems Solved
Revenue by sales channel
Top 10 customers
Monthly profit & loss analysis
Most profitable clinic per city
Second least profitable clinic per state

=>Concepts Used
Advanced CTEs
Window Functions (RANK)
Profit calculation logic
Full join simulation (UNION)
Business analytics queries

=>Tools & Technologies
SQL (MySQL / PostgreSQL compatible)
Relational Database Design
Data Analysis using SQL

=>How to Run
Open MySQL / PostgreSQL
Run schema files first:
Hotel → 01_Hotel_Schema_Setup.sql
Clinic → 03_Clinic_Schema_Setup.sql

Then run queries:
02_Hotel_Queries.sql
04_Clinic_Queries.sql

3.Learning Outcomes
Real-world database design
Writing complex SQL queries
Analytical thinking using SQL
Interview-level problem solving
Understanding business metrics
